belr
------------------------------------------
Belr is Belledonne Communications' language recognition library, written in
C++11.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libbctoolbox1-5.4.116-1bl1
  libbelr-devel-5.4.117-1bl1
  libbelr1-5.4.117-1bl1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libbctoolbox-devel-5.4.116-1bl1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/BelledonneCommunications/belr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/BelledonneCommunications/belr/archive/refs/tags/5.4.117.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack belr-5.4.117-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./belr-5.4.117-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/belr-5.4.117-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/belr-5.4.117-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbelr1-5.4.117-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbelr-devel-5.4.117-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(belr)
  /usr/bin/belr-compiler.exe
  /usr/bin/belr-parse.exe
  /usr/bin/belr-tester.exe
  /usr/share/belr-tester/res/basicgrammar.txt
  /usr/share/belr-tester/res/register.txt
  /usr/share/belr-tester/res/response.txt
  /usr/share/belr-tester/res/sipgrammar.txt
  /usr/share/belr-tester/res/vcardgrammar.txt
  /usr/share/belr/grammars/belr-grammar-example.blr
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/belr.README
  /usr/share/doc/belr/CHANGELOG.md
  /usr/share/doc/belr/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/belr/README.md

(libbelr1)
  /usr/bin/cygbelr-1.dll

(libbelr-devel)
  /usr/include/belr/abnf.h
  /usr/include/belr/belr.h
  /usr/include/belr/grammarbuilder.h
  /usr/include/belr/parser.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/belr/BelrConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/belr/BelrConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/belr/BelrTargets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/belr/BelrTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libbelr.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/belr.pc

